# Implementation Plan: Phase 3 — Course & Curriculum Management

This document details the architecture, design choices, file updates, and verification plan for implementing Phase 3 of the Online Education Platform.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Video Upload Storage**: In development mode, files will be saved locally under the `media/` directory. Presigned URLs will be mocked by serving normal local URLs. Production config can integrate `django-storages` with AWS S3.
> - **Quiz Question Access**: To prevent students from cheating, correct option answers in QuizQuestions are hidden from regular GET requests unless the requesting user is the mentor who owns the course, or an admin.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Component

#### [NEW] [permissions.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/permissions.py)
Create course-specific permission classes to verify ownership:
- `IsCourseMentor`: Allows read/write only to the Mentor associated with the Course. Other authenticated users have read-only access (if course is approved & published).
- `IsModuleMentor` / `IsLessonMentor`: Resolves ownership by traversing up to the parent `Course` object.

#### [NEW] [serializers.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/serializers.py)
Implement serializers for REST representation:
- `QuizQuestionSerializer`: Serializes quiz questions. Hides `correct_option` if user is a student.
- `LessonSerializer`: Handles individual lessons. Excludes sensitive links (`video_url` and `file_attachment`) for non-enrolled students.
- `ModuleSerializer`: Groups lessons under their parent module.
- `CourseSerializer`: Returns detailed course metrics including nested modules/lessons. Includes validations on prices and levels.
- `CourseListSerializer`: Lightweight listing serializer for catalogs.

#### [MODIFY] [views.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/views.py)
Provide REST viewsets:
- `CourseViewSet`: 
  - Standard GET returns only approved & published courses for students.
  - Mentors can view all draft/pending courses they own.
  - Admins can query all courses.
  - Custom actions: `approve` and `reject` (Admin only), `publish` (Mentor only).
- `ModuleViewSet` & `LessonViewSet`: Handle CRUD, restricted to parent course mentor.
- `QuizQuestionViewSet`: Restricted access for editing questions.

#### [MODIFY] [urls.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/urls.py)
Register viewsets to default router:
- `/api/courses/`
- `/api/modules/`
- `/api/lessons/`
- `/api/quiz-questions/`

#### [MODIFY] [admin.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/admin.py)
Register `Course`, `Module`, `Lesson`, `QuizQuestion`, and `Review` with Django admin console.

